cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses an algorithm for inferring hierarchical structure from a sequence of discrete symbols, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves constraints that reduce the size of the grammar, which is a topic in machine learning and data structures, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The algorithm's application to real-world sequences suggests that it may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
